Virtualmin plugin to deploy websites server through Nginx and uWSGI.

Requires Nginx, uWSGI and Virtualenv.

To serve Python 2 applications install uWSGI plugin python and uWSGI plugin python3 for Python 3.
`apt-get install uwsgi-plugin-python`
`apt-get install uwsgi-plugin-python3`

Detailed deployment instruction is in moudule help page.

SSL support is one way: it is either disabled or enabled and all HTTP traffic permanently redirects to HTTPS.

Tested to work with Python 3, Django 1.8.2 under Debian 8.

WARNING: This module does not work under Debian 7, making Python 3.2, uWSGI and Django work together under Debian 7 is a real pain.
